[6/21/17, 5:34:35 PM] Niraj Chaurasia: Fill in the english wherever required or personalize it to your situation and comfortable english.
VO wont know if you are really good at studies or if you are avg students. So dont assume in that way and try to fill him in with details and personalized answers.

Q: How many colleges have you applied/how many admits or how many rejects
3 in USA and 1 in Europe. 1 accept in USA and 1 in Europe. (Do not overstate..just answer to the point first and if still he/she is expecting answer keep on talking more-this applies to all the questions and if you are interrupted..do not ignore and do not keep talking. stop and listen to what is being said next)

Q: Which course/why masters?
Computer science at CMU for the continuation to my background in CS. My current standing in CS requires me to gain more specialized knowledge in this field to make the bes

Q: What is your plan after masters?
Do not talk about OPT first unless asked explicitly. Start with assumption that he is trying to know if you are planning to return or not. >>>>
I plan to come back to Nepal and start my own venture in CS as the field is starting to grow in Nepal and poses many opportunity in coming future/I plan to come back to Nepal and start business with my father and make the best of out the knowledge I gain from my master.

Q: if asked explicitly about OPT>>
Mine is a STEM course and it gives me edge to gain hands on experience in my field of study. I plan to utilize the OPT period and return back to Nepal to further excel (or join you answer to above question)

Q: Why CMU?
The courses like (AI, ML or just lookup 3-4 courses in the CMU website with some background and the professor name) taught by Prof. ABC, Prof. BCD and Prof. XYZ helped me finalize CMU over other admits. Moreover my research interest totally inclines to the research work Prof.XYZ in ...(mention some project by some prof). I plan to work under him/her.

Q: Who is funding your education?
Financial docs are not checked generally so start like this>>>
My father will be supporting me majorly as he has got business with profit of ...... amount per year. Also I have some saving from my work which should support my tickets and some living expenses in first sem (Keep your payslips and IT reuturns ready and do not mention figures unless asked). I also have loan approved from Prodigy Finance (do not mention that its from US or do not mention amount) in case uncertainities arises.

[6/22/17, 5:43:36 AM] Niraj Chaurasia: VISA Experience
******************
Consulate : Chennai
Date : 21/06/2017
University: SUNY Buffalo
Status : Approved.
Dress Code : Formals
Appointment Time : 11:30 am
( Went in by 10 and came out by 10:45)
Counter No:19
VO was a young male.

Me : good morning
Vo : good morning. Pass your docs.
Me : sure . Passed the passport, i20 and servis confirmation.
VO : Is this your first interview?
Me : Yes
VO : How many colleges u applied.
Me : 8 and listed them.
VO : Why suny Buffalo ?
Me : It has a good course structure.....explained about the courses and focus areas
VO : When did you passout ?
Me : 2015
VO : What were you doing since then ?
Me : Working in Infosys.
VO : (Looking at me ) Oh Infosys. (Me thinking did I just say something wrong )
Me : Yeah
VO : Who is your sponsor.
Me : Father
VO : What is your father's annual income.
Me : (Suddenly remembered I said father instead of parent's ) My mother is also working and she is also sponsoring me . My father has an income of xx lakhs and my mother has an income of xx lakhs. (At this time he was looking at me and was carefully listening to me )
VO : What will you do after your masters ?
Me : Will come back to India and work in a Company of my choice with the knowledge gained from my Masters.
VO : Congrats, I am approving ur VISA.
Me : Thank you Sir and left the place ğŸ˜€.
After sometime realized that I forgot to mention about the Education loan.ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£

[11/19/17, 4:27:38 AM] Bikesh Jiju: 1. cook 70% chana in pressure cooker
2. Make proper tadka ( tejpat, jerra, lawang, red mirchi, daalchini) in other pan and fry onions untill red
3. put spices and fry until proper cooked and realese of oilish look then put tamato
4. now Pour 70% cooked chick peas and chicken pieces together in the pan 
5. The trick is chick peas get cooked by the water released by chicken and at the end the tatse is amazing 
6. Serve with roti or naan recomended!

[3/4/20, 8:19:43 PM] Bikesh Jiju: The coronavirus is large in size with a cell diameter of 400-500 micro, so any mask prevents its entry so there is no need to exploit pharmacists to trade with muzzles. The virus does not settle in the air, but on the ground, so it is not transmitted by the air. The coronavirus, when it falls on a metal surface, will live for 12 hours, so washing hands with soap and water well will do the trick. Coronavirus, when it falls on fabrics, stays for 9 hours so washing clothes or exposing them to the sun for two hours is enough for the purpose of killing him. The virus lives on the hands for 10 minutes so putting the alcohol sanitizer in the pocket is enough for the purpose of prevention. If the virus is exposed to a temperature of 26-27Â°C, it will be killed, it does not live in hot areas. Also drinking hot water and exposure to the sun is good enough. Stay away from ice cream and cold food is important. Gargling with warm water and salt kills tonsils and prevents them from leaking into the lungs. Adhering to these instructions is sufficient to prevent the virus. UNICEF #UNICEF â€” with Bitu Mishra Vats.

[3/4/21, 6:33:48 AM] Bikesh Jiju: Sharing my Vaccinations experience this morning. 

1. It takes 20 mins roughly from the time u get in. 
2. Bring given form filled, State Id and insurance card. 
3.They will review the eligibility requirement. Tick on county required option. 
4. After shot, they will ask u to be in store for 10 mins just in case u have any reactions.

Overall very smooth.
